      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:35:7",
      "text": [
        " إِنَّ أَمِيرَ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) كَرِهَ أَنْ تُسْقَى الدَّوَابُّ الْخَمْرَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Khalid, from his father, from Giyas, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said that Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> abhorred that one should quench the wine to the animals’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn Khalid from his father from Ghiyath who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that ’Amir al-Mu’minin, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, disliked one’s making the animals drink wine.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
